vg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juni 28, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wgz1719591021043.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wgz1719591021043.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wgz1719591021043.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rpn1665702893211\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      DDE Syntax Rules\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"rpn1665702893211__dde_syntax_rules_114556\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rpn1665702893211__p_d35687e1_d35688e1_d35689e1\">When you access Uniface as a DDE server, you must observe the following syntax rules for request transactions:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rpn1665702893211__li_d18260e1_d18261e1_d18262e1\">The service name must be the name of the application as returned by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$applname</span>. If no service is specified, the default is <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"uniface\"</code>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rpn1665702893211__li_d18263e1_d18264e1_d18265e1\">The topic name must match the current component.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rpn1665702893211__li_d18266e1_d18267e1_d18268e1\">The first part of the item string is a field name or comma-separated list of field names. This is optionally followed by an entity specification. After the entity name, you can specify the occurrence or occurrences that should be accessed. Item name syntax is shown below:\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__1\">\n Syntax\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__1\">\n field\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__2\">\n Single field in current occurrence. If no entity is specified, the normal Uniface binding rules apply.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__1\">\n field1,field2,field3.entity\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__2\">\n field1, field2, and field3 of current occurrence of entity.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__1\">\n *.entry\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__2\">\n All fields of current occurrence of entity. The entity specification is not optional when you use the \"*\" syntax for fields.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">field1,field2.entity[n]</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">field1 and field2 of occurrence n of entity.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">field1,field2.entity[n:<var class=\"keyword varname\">m</var>]</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">field1 and field2 of occurrence n through <var class=\"keyword varname\">m</var> of entity.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__1\">\n *.entity[*]\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rpn1665702893211__table_d3593e1_d3594e1_d3595e1__entry__2\">\n Every database field of all occurrences of entity.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rpn1665702893211__p_d35690e1_d35691e1_d35692e1\">If links are pasted from the clipboard (for example, with the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Paste Link</span> command), the <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"field.entity\"</code> syntax is used automatically.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/izj1665702893142.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface as a DDE Server</a><p>When Uniface acts as a DDE server, the DDE link must be defined in the client application.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yga1665702577055.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$applname</a><p>Return the name of the Application Shell.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7424442\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7424442\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "DDE Syntax Rules Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 28, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 DDE Syntax Rules When you access Uniface as a DDE server, you must observe the following syntax rules for request transactions: The service name must be the name of the application as returned by $applname . If no service is specified, the default is \"uniface\" . The topic name must match the current component. The first part of the item string is a field name or comma-separated list of field names. This is optionally followed by an entity specification. After the entity name, you can specify the occurrence or occurrences that should be accessed. Item name syntax is shown below: Syntax Meaning field Single field in current occurrence. If no entity is specified, the normal Uniface binding rules apply. field1,field2,field3.entity field1, field2, and field3 of current occurrence of entity. *.entry All fields of current occurrence of entity. The entity specification is not optional when you use the \"*\" syntax for fields. field1,field2.entity[n] field1 and field2 of occurrence n of entity. field1,field2.entity[n: m ] field1 and field2 of occurrence n through m of entity. *.entity[*] Every database field of all occurrences of entity. If links are pasted from the clipboard (for example, with the Paste Link command), the \"field.entity\" syntax is used automatically. Related Links Uniface as a DDE Server When Uniface acts as a DDE server, the DDE link must be defined in the client application. $applname Return the name of the Application Shell. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}